erative (as reported)\". Not in original list but added.\n\nNow we need to answer the questions asked by Agent 1: They asked for reliability and responsibility of A and D (already answered by Agent 2). They also asked for remaining gaps: reliability of D, responsibility of A, teamwork/communication for B, teamwork/communication for C, leadership depth for B and C.\n\nWe can answer these based on our knowledge: Do we have any info about reliability of D? Not explicit. We have no reliability statement. So we can say none. Responsibility of A? No explicit statement. So none. Teamwork/communication for B: we have \"sometimes adopts wrong tone when communicating\", \"pretentious\", \"grumpy/uncooperative\". So we can note that. Teamwork/communication for C: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, but also \"puts concern for others above everything\" and \"creates positive atmosphere\"? Actually that was from agent_1's note: \"creates positive atmosphere\". Not in original list but appears in agent_1's evaluation. So we can note both. Leadership depth for B and C: B has calmness, reliability, but no explicit leadership. C has quick decision making, concern for others, but egocentric. So we can note limited leadership evidence.\n\nThus we can answer those questions.\n\nWe also need to give our vote. Based on evaluation, we might lean toward Candidate B but note concerns. Or maybe Candidate A? Let's weigh: Long-distance flights require reliability (B is 100% reliable), calm under pressure (B and C), technical competence (B good weather, computer; A spatial vision; D problem solving; C attention). Teamwork/communication: B has tone issues; C difficulty communicating but puts concern for others; A unfriendly; D loner. Leadership: A very good leadership; B none; C limited; D weak. Responsibility: D takes responsibility seriously; A unknown; B unknown; C unknown. Overall, B's reliability and calmness are critical, but teamwork issues could be mitigated. C's communication issues could be problematic. A's leadership is strong but interpersonal issues (unfriendly, unorganized) could affect crew. D's responsibility and problem solving but poor leadership and temperament.\n\nThus B seems best overall if we can manage communication style. I will vote Candidate B, with moderate confidence.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE: Summarize answers to the questions, add any additional observations, ask any further clarifications if needed.\n\nWe should also maybe ask about reliability of D and responsibility of A if any other agent has info.\n\nThus final output."}
